package saker.build.thirdparty.saker.rmi.exception
public class RMIRuntimeException extends RuntimeException
saker.build.thirdparty.saker.rmi.exception.RMIRuntimeException
java.lang.RuntimeException
java.lang.Exception
java.lang.Throwable
java.lang.Object
java.io.Serializable
RMIShutdownRequestDeniedException, RMICallFailedException, RMICallForbiddenException, RMIContextVariableNotFoundException, RMIIOFailureException, RMIInvalidConfigurationException, RMIObjectTransferFailureException, RMIProxyCreationFailedException, RMIStackTracedException
Common superclass for all RMI related exceptions.

Throwing instances of this class manually might result in undefined operation of the RMI runtime.

public RMIRuntimeException()
Documentation included from: RuntimeException
Constructs a new runtime exception with null as its detail message. The cause is not initialized, and may subsequently be initialized by a call to Throwable.initCause(Throwable).
public RMIRuntimeException(String message)
Documentation included from: RuntimeException
Constructs a new runtime exception with the specified detail message. The cause is not initialized, and may subsequently be initialized by a call to Throwable.initCause(Throwable).
messagethe detail message. The detail message is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getMessage() method.
public RMIRuntimeException(String message, Throwable cause)
Documentation included from: RuntimeException
Constructs a new runtime exception with the specified detail message and cause.

Note that the detail message associated with cause is not automatically incorporated in this runtime exception's detail message.

messagethe detail message (which is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getMessage() method).
causethe cause (which is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getCause() method). (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)

Documentation included from: RuntimeException

messagethe detail message.

enableSuppressionwhether or not suppression is enabled or disabled

1.7
public RMIRuntimeException(Throwable cause)
Documentation included from: RuntimeException
Constructs a new runtime exception with the specified cause and a detail message of (cause==null ? null : cause.toString()) (which typically contains the class and detail message of cause). This constructor is useful for runtime exceptions that are little more than wrappers for other throwables.
causethe cause (which is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getCause() method). (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)
